sub_title: Master degree in Local Development | University of Padua
summary:
As someone taught me in Sierra Leone: "If you listen to the noise of the market, you won't buy anything".

If you wonder about my professional profile, I can't find just one word to define myself. My academic background is in Mental Health. I am now studying Local Development. My life experience taught me about Project Management, fundraising, diplomacy, child protection, resilience, policy writing. Recently, I also reinvented myself, and I've learned how to serve customers. 
I understood that I have just one passion, which is to be an instrument for others' successes. 
I can be everything, as long as I am working within a team, and I can be an element of support for others. 

Said so, if you want me to describe what I did, and I can do:  I coordinated multiple development projects, including relationships with Government Institutions and Donors. My main interest is in projects about psychosocial support to adults, youths, and children experiencing severe traumas. I am also a Receptionist. 

Now, I wish you a peaceful day/night.
